comment: American judges seem to be rather pathetic. A British High Court judge would never self-reference in any way whatsoever, let alone say how horrified they might be or, worst of all, apparently tear up. They say the defendant's name and then list the crimes they've been found guilty of and objectively put the gravity of those crimes in perspective according to their relative level of depravity, accurately condemning the criminal in the process. Then, they'll drop the sentence accordingly, conscious of current parliamentary guidelines and precedent. That's how you judge. You don't explain how awful it all is to the criminal and wind yourself up in front of the cameras to the point where you're ready to lay the punishment down. That is just extremely undignified and strange, and, more importantly, open to further interpretation (and appeal). In other words, it's not very good.

comment:
If it saves another life, please please be very careful who you have children with ‚Ä¶ 

Many years ago I dated a psychopath. He was evil. I‚Äôm still alive but it left scars for a long time and I still have anxiety when alone and close my blinds and curtains and don‚Äôt like going outside the house in the dark. I never used to be like that, but years later I‚Äôm still nervous.  I‚Äôm glad I didn‚Äôt have children with him. It would have ended badly ‚Ä¶ 

Im a 40 year old lady now, happily married but had some experiences. I wish I chose my partner a long time ago - I chose him for his principles and beliefs.  When I was young I made stupid choices and ignored red flags. 

There is no way a girl would pick a partner like this guy unless she really liked his bad boy image, bad gangsta attitude and bizarre hairstyle.  Pick a guy who will make a great dad‚Ä¶ someone who has principles and is gracious and isn‚Äôt a narcissist like this. If they don‚Äôt murder you in cold blood like this guy, they will still emotionally and physically abuse you for life.  Life is hell with a psychopath. They have no empathy or feeling and are the epitome of evil.  Many people die at the hands of domestic violence every day, but you can protect yourself if you can identify a controller and get rid of him before you‚Äôre under his spell. Women can be abusive too and can be very cruel so whether you‚Äôre male or female please be careful

comment: Luckily he will most likely be shanked in prison; neither prisoners 'or' guards take lightly not only child killers, but even worse inmates who killed their 'own' child. That's a serious red line in prison culture and this guy most likely won't survive past a few months 'if' even that long. I'd bet first week. But what's even 'more' tragic is this guy got a prison sentence?! Why didn't he get capital punishment? No sane society lets people like this continue living, they have lost their right to life by committing such heinous crimes. And society is victimized 'twice', first by the crime, then by having to pay for the criminal's upkeep. Capital punishment with no appeal needs to be applied much more often in our society to a much wider group of crimes such as home invasion, use of a deadly weapon during a crime, most types of rape, car jacking, kidnapping, pedophilia; violent criminals have nothing left to contribute and their continued existence in prison is just a drain on our society where the money could be used for people who are deserving of help.

comment:
It's important to try and make the accused to understand the reality of what was done so that they can gather whether there's any remorse. Thing is some people quite literally just don't care. Whether they have blocked out all emotion or just literally are in a state of mind where they feel no emotional connection to what they did its very important as it determines the sentence someone receives and also gives somewhat of understanding or closure to those affected.

It's shocking the type of things people will do but we really need to be understanding why. What pushes these people to do what they do. It's quite easy for anyone to say they are evil, their actions may be just that but no one is truly born evil.. Evil actions come from somewhere.. We need to work on providing better support and care for all. In my opinion this is the only way we will see less and less of these types of crimes. If you take these people as a baby and give them a very happy safe and provvilaged upbringing they would be a complete different human being. Even I would and even you would.

This isn't an excuse for what people do but it's so important that people understand that, I feel like our world is very reactive when it comes to people and their suffering. Things are dealt with afterwards and I hear things all the time that "should" have been avoided. Perhaps governments need to invest more in providing safe situations for people to talk about their feelings. School shootings for example.. People who blame things like video games or horror movies are just burying their heads in the sand. If they caused school shootings then why can the billions of others not shoot up a school? It's because these people have very troubled mental States usually because they have also suffered horrific events in their lives. Some people who I've heard have murdered someone get told they are sick and should rot etc however no one seems to care they had no parents and was sexually abused from a young age.. Bullied in school fighting for every meal. Actions and situations can shape each and everyone of us to do unthinkable things. I just hope if you are still reading and every find yourself in a dark place speak out and find help, there is always help there for you.

comment: In US, African Americans are more likely than white Americans to be arrested; once arrested, they are more likely to be convicted; and once convicted, and they are more likely to experience lengthy prison sentences. African-American adults are 5.9 times as likely to be incarcerated than whites and Hispanics are 3.1 times as likely. As of 2001, one of every three black boys born in that year could expect to go to prison in his lifetime, as could one of every six Latinos‚Äîcompared to one of every seventeen white boys. The source of such disparities is deeper and more systemic than explicit racial discrimination. The United States in effect operates two distinct criminal justice systems: one for white people and another for people of color. US is still a racist nation.

comment:
I am no hero
nor do I identify myself as a defender of "good", a lawbringer, or anything that relates to the preservation of the concept called "justice". 
But it is monsters like this one I would kill on sight. They don't have anything other than their body. They don't feel anything, they just do things for the sheer pleasure of it. Even when she was making such a speech that I've never expected a judge to make. Nothing. Not a droplet of regret. Just some fake nods to look like he was saying "I understand" when all he was listening to were probably his worthless thoughts. I know it. 

Death penalty can be cruel because we are flawed. We can kill innocents when lies are spoken and facts hidden. But things like that abomination standing in the court room, they have to be eliminated. Exceptions have to be made to have them terminated. They cannot be "fixed". Lifelong detention is a form of pity it doesn't deserve in the slightest. It doesn't feel pain either, so torture too is a blessing. It just has to get that lethal injection and die in its eternal loneliness. The corpse thrown to maggots or animals so that it can do some good after its demise. And perhaps a good drink after the deed as such a menace is eliminated and therefore one danger removed. And the people who have succumbed to him, too gentle for their own good, they should be mourned more.

comment:
The second crime is not torturing him. Facts. Society deserves and apology. It is foolish to not have a system which does not exact 10 fold the horror on those who torture the undeserving. Of course, tragedies will still occur, but every human being should know that if they commit such crimes, there fellow human beings will make them truly truly pay. 
Of all things in the world, torture is a world of its own. 
It is often used for evil, but like every action, it is neutral. Context determines the righteousness of an act. Plenty of people deserve to die, and have their bodies destroyed, but there are a subset for which an instant death would be a gift. Demons of the world, demons like this man, do not fear, for they do not believe,  that there are those who could literally destroy their soul. 
Through torture this man could be turned into a daycare teacher that we could trust around kids, a person whose personhood has been erased and reprogrammed through repetitive trauma. Completely withdrawn into a coma like state, we could reprogram this man to lick the bottom of the judges shoes and bark every time court was in session. 
Let him thank whoever or whatever he believes for the beatings he will get in prison, for if he was left to me, he would be mercilessly, brutally, and most completely, brainwashed beyond all comprehension.
I have spoken

comment:
This is why I am a believer in the death penalty. The concept of law and the death sentence was designed to showcase that in the law of "Lex Talionus" there is no equal measure of a life taken in cold blood than the death of the perpetrator if found guilty. This shows that human life has value and allowing one who acts heinously to continue breathing after a murderous [not manslaughter or accidental killing] act against another is not justice. 

I mean think of it this way. This guy gets to eat and drink in jail. His girlfriend and daughter are still dead in the ground. He gets to sleep soundly and makes friends in prison. His girlfriend and daughter are still dead in the ground. He gets to read and find little things to have pleasure in despite his circumstances. His girlfriend and dead daughter are still dead in the ground. He gets to laugh, He gets to cry, He gets to feel, but he doesn't get to die. 

Capital punishment is not a human against human punishment. It is meant to showcase and execute the universal moral law above humanity. comment:
When the case has been tried, and the conviction returned, it is the job of the judge to ensure that the law is followed, that the verdict is clear, and that the sentence is commensurate with the crime as prescribed by law. It is not the job of the judge to pontificate or to provide extra-legal commentary on the nature of the case or on the character of the convicted defendant. 
Judge, for God's sake, just render the verdict, impose the required sentence and then shut the hell up! Every time you open you mouth at this stage, you open the door for a potentially successful appeal by the scumbag in question, because you can't restrain yourself.

I am Canadian, I am Christian, but I am also a father, husband and human, but saying all that, this man deserves the death penalty. He also deserves to suffer, and if there is a here after, and god do I hope that is so, there is no doubt in my mind that he will suffer in the after life.  However that‚Äôs not enough, not even close.  

I understand that in prison there is a code. This code, honour code, that they have has limits to what they will put up with.  There is honour among thieves, some crimes are unforgivable, even for rapists and murderers.  They don‚Äôt put up with child molesters, pedophiles or people who harm children, especially children with special needs.  What they do to those criminals is horrific, they make those people suffer, and those who exact that suffering are treated as heroes, even though it will add to their time in prison.

So I hope this guy gets put in with all the other prisoners, and that the prison guards turn a blind eye to what ever happens to this cruel person.  Then and only then, after years of that torture do they allow this thing to die.

comment:
I'm all for the judge saying at the sentencing what the factors of the sentence are in her mind... but as a matter of dealing impartial justice, I don't feel like judges should be making these diatribes at a sentencing. I know nobody wants a judge without emotions... but when the proceedings are over and it's time for the judge to do the act of sentencing a MEASURED and fair sentence... isn't it inappropriate to be emoting like this? Just tell us the factors you took under consideration, offer a BRIEF statement to the victims... and say the sentence.
 
I get the distinct sense that the judge is enjoying dressing down the defendant here... and I understand how one WOULD derive satisfaction from it... however, it's the judge's primary job to ensure a fair trial and a measured sentence to a convicted person. A colder and more professional demeanor is far more appropriate when you are representing law and due process.
 
Say whatever you want to the news after the trial is over, but during the trial... stick the damn landing. You're a judge... not a blogger. Deal the justice and move on. Expressing your catharsis or grief as a judge is not a legitimate part of your job.

comment:
If I was a rich man, I'd buy a small island then build a large castle on it.

The purpose of this castle would be to facilitate animals like this guy. Not so they get fed three times a day and have a comfortable bed to sleep in. It would be from my own pocket and not the pocket of the taxes.

On this island, no rules apply, no laws and no gods would exist. Only the human instinct of survival. 

I would pay employees to physically and mentally torture each and every one of these prisoners so they can feel the pain and suffering they caused to their victims, the families and the communities.

They will live from bare minimum food, just enough to keep them alive but not enough for them to feel comfortable. If they want water, they better pray it rains so they can lick it from the dirty floor they walk on. They will sleep on the hard cold ground, in a 2x1m cell with bars, with absolutely no light.

Their only way out? They can put themselves out of their misery, they can ask to have it done for them or they can go to the end of the island and see if they can swim to the mainland. On the edge of the island would be a stadium, where one A-hole can duke it out with another A-hole to see who's the biggest A-Hole. The purpose of this, you ask? One less mouth to feed and one free cell for the next animal to enter the island. 

But of course when a monster decides to take a person's life, there is NOTHING that makes up for losing a loved one. No amount of money, no amount of sentence and not even the death penalty makes it even. 

Stay humble fellow humans, don't be hurting each other, we all deserve to live safe and happy lives. ‚ô°

comment: You know something, I'm glad that he got life because death would have been way too quick for a monster like that. There was no emotion to the fact that his daughter was dead, murdered in such an horrific way or that his son was nearly murdered also as well as the fact that their mother was also murdered. The mother sounded like a beautiful soul who obviously loved her children and wanted her daughter to feel like the wonderful little princess that she was. I say that I'm glad that he's not given the death penalty (even though he deserves it) is because he will never be able to sit under a tree ever again or feel the grass under his feet, feel a woman in his arms or enjoy a cool beer and what's more, I feel that someone, somewhere will let slip of what a Brutal thing he did to his kids and their mom and there will be no one willing to protect his back. I hope, I pray, that every single day and night of his incarceration is one of torment and abuse, where he has to watch his every single move to the point that he wishes that he was given the death penalty, because scum like that deserves it. My heart and thoughts goes out to the victims and of course their families.

comment: This is why we need a MANDATORY death penalty in EVERY state!! And no more of this BS appealing for 30 years. If a person is convicted and it's 100 percent for sure the person did commit the murder or murders, then you sentence him to prison for 1 year and on any day during that year his execution will be carried out. The murderer will not be told of execution until day of. Now that is how you serve justice. I am tired of countless proven murderers getting to live for 30-40 years or longer in prison waiting to exhaust all appeals. And I am really TIRED of snowflake liberals who cry for murderers who might have suffered a little bit at execution. WGAF?? What about the victims that suffered for who knows how long?? It's time America grows a pair of balls and starts enforcing the laws of the land and stops catering to all snowflakes out in the world.

comment:
It's easy to say this guy is evil.
Trust me.....I 100% get that impulse. But....I think it's more complex, unfortunately.
YES, he absolutely should be locked away for the rest of his life. He is a danger to other people. He cannot be free.
But....he strikes me as severely psychologically damaged. He's clearly mentally ill. Maybe a sociopath or psychopath. I'm just grateful I'm not afflicted with psychopathy. In a weird way, I feel genuine sorrow for people who are. They literally have zero empathy....and indeed don't even know what it is that's missing in their mind. They cannot understand what comes naturally to the rest of us. Seems like a horrific life to me.

And while such people are quite dangerous....and we must protect ourselves from them.....I sure hope at some point in the future, medical science advances to a point where we can CURE psychopathy. Until then, calling such people evil just feels pointless. It's such an unhelpful meaningless word.....meant to soothe US instead of actually addressing the root cause of that evil.

Anyway.....sorry to rant. I just felt odd while watching this Ronnie Oneal guy while the judge said what she said. He seemed.....detached....depersonalized....oddly sociopathic. What a nightmare all around.....  sigh....

comment: If I may do a little deduction, from the limited amount of information given in this video we hear that prior to the murders he was staying with the victims, recovering from a gun wound. That tells me someone was trying to kill him. His other relations would not allow him to stay with them for reasons I can only speculate upon, being they were either fearful of him or fearful of his attacker wanting to finish the attempt on his life. Enter the victims. The mother allows him to recuperate at her residence due to some history they shared, word got around as to his whereabouts and they pay him a visit. He currently was absent at the times of the murders or simply selfishly abandoned the victims. The victims were murdered as a message to him. Im not sure if the recording revealed it to be him specifically, which I didnt hear that it was presented as evidence. The sum is this; he is a victim of a toxic culture specifically the aspect of not snitching, even to save his own life. I could very well be very wrong and I am so sorry for the loss of this family. I just wish I had all of the information.

comment: 6:00 ...sorry for being logical here: If a soul chooses their life before being born, KNOWING what such life will be like, then such a soul would have to suffer and experience everything they will experience in life before they get born. If this was not the case how could they know what they would have to suffer in the chosen coming life? You can`t imagine - and therefor agree to it and choose it - unimaginable pain or joy without having experienced it before. And besides that: Why would a soul choose such a life in the first place?! If it was brave enough to choose - knowingly - such a life, then it didn`t have to live such a life to learn to be brave etc.  Just shows how deluded and irrational even people can think who have been trained to think in very logical and consistent ways as lawyers etc. are.    Further  more: If one knows what the life to be lived contains, then it is a necessary implication that life is determined, that is: no free will exists which could change fate. This would be true for victims and offenders. No free will, no culpability it would seem. If you have no choice than to do or suffer what is destined how can one be responsible for what one does or suffers? If one is free to choose a future destiny: Why choose to say yes or no? Is one offered good and bad possible lifes? Why would anyone choose a bad life? If it was to learn something (what could suffering teach you more than that suffering shouldn`t exist?) why do I need to suffer the fully anticipated future life? Such an anticipation, if of any relevance to choosing would imply the learning effect allredy.

comment: The court system is unjust, this is not justice. The death penalty should be mandatory for any premeditated murder. No more death row, no more housing evil inmates. The process of this all is a waste of time and resources. All there should be is an investigation and trail if evidence shows the person did it. Many defense attorneys are greedy and treat their job as a day at the office as they defend rapist, murderers, child predators and other sicko's from due capital punishment. Most prisoners go to prison and just reform to the prison system being their new home, it is not punishing at all. Thinking this man will get punished in prison for what he's done is a lie, that is a myth brought on by Hollywood. There is a low chance of anyone doing anything to him for hurting a child. You people really need to step up and force the justice system to act right in your areas. People can protest a bunch of nonsense all year round but when it comes to the most sick and sadistic people, nobody organizes to just rid the world of them as it should be. Someone convinced you life in prison is a better alternative than capital punishment, you should look up who and what that was.

comment:
The judge was a bit harsh on him. He was just acting his race. It‚Äôs that damn MOA-A gene. 
Monoamine oxidase A is an enzyme that breaks down important neurotransmitters in the brain, including dopamine, norepinephrine, and serotonin. The enzyme is regulated by monoamine oxidase A gene (MAOA). Humans have various forms of the gene, resulting in different levels of enzymatic activity. People with the low-activity form (MAOA-L) produce less of the enzyme, while the high-activity form (MAOA-H) produces more of the enzyme.
Studies done in the late 70‚Äôs concluded that blacks are five times more likely to have the MOA-A gene than whites, and six times more than Asians. Read A Troublesome Inheritance by Nicholas Wade. Of course the woke left has been doing hit pieces on his work for decades but the science is solid.

comment: What I do not understand about this display is the reason for it. Obviously, it doesn't take an expert to know that this man is absolutely insane, and absolutely insane people are quite capable of committing absolutely insane acts. Killing any defenseless person, such as a disabled child, is, in a couple of words, truly, absolutely insane. Will raping this man Oneal in prison bring the child and mother back? To say any more about the matter to me seems to suggest that there is something more to be gained by recounting truly, absolutely insane acts. Who in my view should care to participate in such a thing is beyond my imagination. As a black person, who must necessarily recall how blacks were aided and abetted by law for centuries to such treatment by people, alleged to be sane, raises the following question: when will the courts restore that of our humanity, as the descendants of slavery, which was stolen and the harm of which can be traced to our maltreatment today by this very system some centuries ago?  My son has been kept away from me and his black family by the white family whose members among the family are lawyers for over 30 years. To say the least, my son has been completely brainwashed. Will these people responsible be ever charged with crimes against humanity for their criminal deeds? Probably not. Whatever happened to the white woman responsible for the death of Emmett Till? The display of emotion is but a ruse folks. Much worse goes on in our system to innocent persons with diagnosed mental health diseases on a daily basis. No money, wrong color, no justice. Sorry to bring it up. Thank you. No comments?

comment:
The Gospel of Salvation/Warnings

JESUS CHRIST is the only Lord and Savior this whole creation needs. Please turn to Jesus Christ and get saved now while his grace is still merciful! 

John 3:16
‚ÄúFor God so loved the world, that he gave his only Son, that whoever believes in him should not perish but have eternal life‚Äù.

Isaiah 45:18
 ‚ÄúFor this is what the Lord says‚Äî
he who created the heavens, he is God;
he who fashioned and made the earth, he founded it; he did not create it to be empty, but formed it to be inhabited he says:
‚ÄúI am the Lord,
    and there is no other‚Äù. 

Deuteronomy 32:39
‚ÄúSee now that I myself am he!
    There is no god besides me.
I put to death and I bring to life,
    I have wounded and I will heal,
    and no one can deliver out of my hand‚Äù. 

Philippians 2:8-11
‚ÄúAnd being found in human form, he humbled himself by becoming obedient to the point of death, even death on a cross. Therefore God has highly exalted him and bestowed on him the name that is above every name, so that at the name of Jesus every knee should bow, in heaven and on earth and under the earth, and every tongue confess that Jesus Christ is Lord, to the glory of God the Father‚Äù. 

JESUS CHRIST WAS GOD IN THE FLESH; Son of God. 

John 1:1-5
‚ÄúIn the beginning was the Word, and the Word was with God, and the Word was God. He was with God in the beginning. Through him all things were made; without him nothing was made that has been made. In him was life, and that life was the light of all mankind. The light shines in the darkness, and the darkness has not overcome it‚Äù.

John 1:14 
‚ÄúThe Word became flesh and made his dwelling among us. We have seen his glory, the glory of the one and only Son, who came from the Father, full of grace and truth‚Äù. 

How to get SALVATION (be saved):

1. Admit that you are a sinner.
Romans 3:32 
 ‚ÄúFor all have sinned and fall short of the glory of God‚Äù. 
Romans 6:23 
‚ÄúFor the wages of sin is death‚Äù.

2. Believe that Jesus paid for your sin at the cross.
Romans 5:8 
‚ÄúBut God demonstrates His own love for us: while we were still sinners, Christ died for us‚Äù. 
Romans 6:23 
‚Äúbut the free gift of God is eternal life in Christ Jesus‚Äù. 
Ephesians 2:8-9
‚ÄúFor it is by grace you have been saved, through faith‚Äîand this is not from yourselves, it is the gift of God‚Äînot by works, so that no one can boast.‚Äù 

3. Confess that Jesus is the Son of God, and commit your life to him. 
Romans 10:9 
‚ÄúThat if you confess with your mouth that Jesus is Lord and believe in your heart that God raised him from the dead, you will be saved‚Äù.  

4. Repent (What does repent mean and do? To repent is a change of mind, that leads to a change of heart, that leads to a change in actions. This ‚Äúchange‚Äù involves both a turning from sin and a turning to God.)
Luke 13:3 
‚ÄúBut unless you repent, you too will all perish‚Äù. 
Acts 3:19 
‚ÄúRepent, then, and turn to God, so that your sins may be wiped out, that times of refreshing may come from the Lord‚Äù. 
2 Peter 3:9 
‚ÄúThe Lord is not slow in keeping his promise, as some understand slowness. Instead he is patient with you, not wanting anyone to perish, but everyone to come to repentance‚Äù. 

Once you come to Salvation then comes baptism. (Baptism is an act in which symbolizes one‚Äôs renewal/purification and becomes a child of God with the power of the Holy Spirit through water, whether the water is poured on to the forehead or one‚Äôs body is immersed into it. This symbolizes the death of our flesh with Christ and our new life through Jesus by the power of the Holy Spirit.)

Acts 2:38
Peter replied, ‚ÄúRepent and be baptized, every one of you, in the name of Jesus Christ for the forgiveness of your sins. And you will receive the gift of the Holy Spirit.‚Äù

Galatians 2:20 
‚Äú¬†I have been crucified with Christ and I no longer live, but Christ lives in me. The life I now live in the body, I live by faith in the Son of God, who loved me and gave himself for me.‚Äù

Galatians 3:26-27
‚ÄúSo in Christ Jesus you are all children of God through faith, for all of you who were baptized into Christ have clothed yourselves with Christ.‚Äù

1 Peter 3:21 
‚ÄúAnd this water symbolizes baptism that now saves you also‚Äînot the removal of dirt from the body but the pledge of a clear conscience toward God. It saves you by the resurrection of Jesus Christ.‚Äù

WARNINGS!!!
Anyone who does not have Jesus Christ will always be condemned and their righteous deeds are like filthy rags. 

Romans 1:8 ‚ÄúThere is therefore now no condemnation to those who are in Christ Jesus, who do not walk according to the flesh, but according to the Spirit‚Äù.

Isaiah 64:6 ‚ÄúAll of us have become like one who is unclean, and all our righteous acts are like filthy rags; we all shrivel up like a leaf, and like the wind our sins sweep us away‚Äù. 

Do not worship/sacrifice to other gods; you will only bring harm to yourself. 

Jeremiah 25:6
‚Äúand do not go after other gods to serve them and to worship them, and do not provoke Me to anger with the work of your hands, and I will do you no harm‚Äù. 

Deuteronomy 8:19 
‚ÄúIt shall come about if you ever forget the Lord your God and go after other gods and serve them and worship them, I testify against you today that you will surely perish‚Äù.

1 Corinthians 10:20 
‚ÄúNo, I imply that what pagans sacrifice they offer to demons and not to God. I do not want you to be participants with demons‚Äù. 

TAKE HEED NOW!!!
Jesus Christ wants you to have a personal relationship with him. He cares and loves you more than his own life that he gave it up for you to be saved. Jesus Christ is the ultimate sacrifice for all mankind; to atoned away all of our sins with his precious life and blood, that we may share in his Kingdom (1 John 2:2 ‚ÄúHe is the propitiation for our sins, and not for ours only but also for the sins of the whole world‚Äù). 
Jesus Christ is not about being religious but to be in unity with him and allow him to deliver you from the bondage that this sinful body (flesh) is doomed for; eternal hell (John 3:36 ‚ÄúWhoever believes in the Son has eternal life; whoever does not obey the Son shall not see life, but the wrath of God remains on him‚Äù). 
Only through Jesus Christ will you ever get to heaven (John 10:9 ‚ÄúI am the door. If anyone enters by me, he will be saved and will go in and out and find pasture‚Äù). Seek Jesus Christ only: no other gods can save you from God‚Äôs wrath. God‚Äôs wrath is not a joke or to be taken lightly (Hebrews 10:31 ‚ÄúIt is a dreadful thing to fall into the hands of the living God‚Äù). Remember he is our Creator and all things are possible with him (Matthew 19:26). 

May God bless you and soften your heart to discern the truth that is in Christ Jesus, the Lord of Lords and King of Kings; the Savior of this world.

A giggle and a smirk! 2:35 If there was evidence that even his parents didn't want him at their home; then they knew he was unwell and dangerous. 3:01 He was recovering from a drive by shooting and thought that he had been 'specifically targeted' and suffered paranoid delusions. How come the police Victim Support Unit was not following up on his recovery with regards to the shooting? 4:06 This is just ridiculous. Everything the judge is saying. What does her mother "trying so hard to make her feel like a princess" have to do with anything? Is she suggesting that if she had been a bad mother, the brutal killing of she and the child would be less disturbing? This man is severely mentally ill. Spare us! 'Faith, Love, Hope got splattered with blood.' What is it that she's trying to do here?! 5:31 See I don't understand any of this. Is this judge a failed actress who had Hollywood dreams or something? It's as though they feel the need to have to 'teach' the public why it's a terrible thing for a child to be brutally killed with an axe. I just can't believe it! 5:46 It's as though she's trying to 'educate' him as to why what he did was wrong. Either he doesn't have mental capacity and doesn't know right from wrong, or he's got to live with it for the rest of his life. What she's doing serves no purpose for either scenario! SHOCKING! 6:04 She 'read somewhere and doesn't know if it's true or not'??! But anyway; she's a judge. So I guess if she reads things 'somewhere' we have to take them seriously. 6:13 And 'emotionally', she totally looks like she's acting! She looks like she's trying to launch a movie career or something! So what's the round-up? We know that American kids are safe now? Is she gonna call for a change in the law so that something gets done for small children who are brutally raped so that perpetrators get arrested and the child gets lifelong therapy? comment:
Haveing a special needs child means this mother had no choice but to deal with multiple government entities. Entities we fund to provide services for the disabled. Services that no longer exist including school for millions of special needs children. This has resulted in millions of mother's living in isolation while being a caregiver 24/7. 
This woman had no way to escape. She probably lost touch with most of her friends and family. Even if she hadn't, friends and family can't simply take in a special needs child for a variety of reasons that are nobody's fault. 
We fund programs so the general public thinks their taxes are taking care of lazy people. In reality billions of dollars aren't being used to provide services for special needs children so that parents aren't stuck in a bad situation which could simply be poverty or in this case a dangerous partner. 
Where was this woman supposed to go with child in tow to get away from this man?

comment:
Anyone ever see the movie "Papillion" with Steve McQueen and Dustin Hoffman??

Multiple life sentences without parole should follow the McQueen's character confinement parameters.......

........an 8 x 10 ft room that is always lit with a recessed bulb.  The door is solid steel with a small slit to pass food trays.  Nobody talks to the prisoners, only a whistle is used yo alert them to feeding time.  No one ever enters the cells other than to remove the body.  If the prisoner soils his cell......he gets to live with it unless willing to clean it himself.

Their food is bare, tasteless, subsistence rations and water.

They get a flea-infested straw mat and moth-eaten blanket for comfort. 

No books, magazines, entertainment or conversation of any kind is allowed.  Every eight months, they get to stick their heads out for a head shave and delousing. 

But, being the humanitarian I am, I'd add two more things.

1)  a steel U-bolt embedded in the seven foot ceiling that can just be reached by standing on the concrete shelf that acts as a bed.

2)  a seven foot length of rope.

The prisoner decides when, and therefore, there is no blood on the State, or on the hands of Justice.

Added bonus.......since none of them have any experience with this mode of suicide, they will generally slowly and painfully strangle to death, rather than a sudden neck snap.

comment:
The Soul's Code by James Hillman.
This is the book that Judge Michelle Sisco  could not recall the name of in this moment.

It is a profound book of insight and gorgeous philosophy of reality and spirituality. For some readers it is healing, making sense of the ungliness and beauty of life. For all readers it is a gift of perspective. The Soul's Code is among the books I treasure. It gave me the perspective to see in myself the potential of forgiveness and deeper love, and I have lived accordingly since my eyes left the last page.

This video made me shed a tear because I understand what Michelle said. This was a human moment superceding the judicial moment. She spoke in total disgust of that man's hideous tendril way down to Hell.
If any of you reading this have an interest in imbuing your lives with enriching perspective, read The Soul's Code.

comment:
Sometimes, the darkest corners harbor the brightest lights.  This case, with all the tragedy and soullessness that consumed it, introduced us to one of the bravest, remarkable people I have personally ever encountered, an example of unexpected love and humanity filled with hope and a reminder of what true service to the people looks like from someone who carries the passion and professionalism required when they take an oath to serve.  
The son in this case will always be one of my heroes as I don‚Äôt know I will ever witness such strength and bravery again.  He leaves me without words.  The detective who adopted that son afterward gives me faith in the common good of man and reminds us of what it looks like when love conquers all.  And, the judge sheds light on how institutions in our government are supposed to operate and carry out its duties for the good of the individuals intended and its citizens.  She exhibited the utmost professionalism and fairness throughout, and leaves us with the empathy and passion in her words that so many of us are feeling.  I wish nothing but grace, peace and prosperity for each of these amazing individuals.  I hope they know the impact they have had on so many of us across the country, and across the world.

comment:
People usually look at the person who committed an atrocity like this and say... What a terrible person!
But think about this for a minute.... This man wasnt born like this. He was raised like this. He has thoughts, feelings, and emotions like everybody else. What things are we doing in society to breed people who think like this man? What did this guy go through for him to think that what he was doing was a good idea? This man created this world view from his environment. And how was this environment created?
Think about the pressures that are created by the people who control the fundamental aspects of our lives. The people who make sure that out attention is focused on material things and promote self consciousness. The people who make sure that the majority of people struggle to make enough money to get by. The people who create an environment where people are too busy trying to survive to pay attention and do something about it.
Its so easy to point a finger and say... What a terrible person!
But we cant point that finger at that person without pointing that finger at ourselves.
The truth is, we have lost touch of the things that really matter in our lives. We let people scare us into sacrificing our liberties/ freedoms. This put a huge clamp down on our pursuit to a good life. And you can bet that situations like this will permeate through our culture as a result.

comment: To everyone brushing this off as him being possessed by demons or having hatred towards him I encourage you to pray for his soul if you are religious and to think logically about this situation if you are not. I pity him because he is pathetic.  I don't necessarily feel sad for Ronnie, but I feel sad of course for his victims and the sad, sick world that created Ronnie. I feel sad for the thought of Ronnie as child traumatized by rape. I think he should be locked up forever not just for what he's done but also because of the risk he is to society.  With that said, having seen footage from parts of the trial, it's clear he's not possessed by demons or evil because the devil is in him.  I'm not a member of a religion but I was, and I know if there is a devil he will not come as a scary monster but as a smooth con artist. The devil is in cold and calculating individuals who know how to effectively manipulate people.  They are the one's who know right from wrong and happily choose wrong anyway, I call it evil and religious people call it the devil.  Ronnie is unable to feel remorse because like all sociopaths he experienced trauma as a child since he was raped by extended family members and was also the victim of a random shooting (Psychopaths are born, sociopaths are made).  He also demonstrates low intellectual functioning, and has impulse control problems, also not uncommon among trauma victims. He was ruled incompetent to stand trial and sent for hospitalization for a couple years before he improved enough to be deemed competent.  Some people think people fake insanity because they can got off easier that way, and they can't.    Not guilty by reason of insanity, which he didn't use as a defense btw, is still for the purpose of the courts a guilty plea since the plea requires that its accepted they committed the act but were incompetent at the time.  Most insanity pleas serve longer sentences for the same crimes convicted by someone deemed competent because with an insanity plea there is no imposed limits to their sentence and they can be kept until they die if no doctor panels agree they no longer pose a threat (google it before you argue).  Ronnie was borderline incompetent throughout the trial as evidenced by his clear fails at trying to defend himself, which was against the court's advice.  Ronnie needs to be locked away until he passes, but while I think he's fully to blame for his actions I don't think he's fully to blame for the person he is because he was a broken human being since childhood.  I guess it's easier for some people to be mad at him than it is for them to recognize the sadness and sickness in the world that created him.

comment:
No! Here is the worst case: A Judge has set a tentative trial date for February 2022 for Curtis Reeves, the former Tampa police officer accused of shooting and killing Chad Oulson at a movie theater in 2014. 8 years after the fact! 

Chad, who was a white man married with children,   was unarmed and texting on his phone during the movie, which prompted Reeves to start an argument which escalated. The perp has been under house arrest on an ankle monitor awaiting trial all this time! WTF?

In the Ronnie Oneal  case there was Justice because the perp was black, with no connection to law enforcement. But in the Reeves case, since he is an ex-cop in his 70's, they are dragging it out so that he can spend time with his family, hoping he'll die of natural causes before he has to go to prison. That's why the self-rightous rant by this Judge doesn't impress me. In Tampa, like many parts of the country, Justice is not blind ... but selectively delivered!
